cardiovascular disease and 501 from coronary heart disease. Neither the history 
of back complaints nor chronic low back pain predicted mortality.
CONCLUSION: That low back pain does not affect longevity disagrees with the 
hypothesis that atherosclerosis resulting in death from cardiovascular disease 
is etiologically linked to low back pain.

