included infection and catheter failure. Infection occurred in 26 patients (18%) 
with 32 catheters (14%) and resulted in removal of 25 catheters. Ninety-three 
catheters (42%) failed, and 63 catheters (28%) were removed because of failure.
CONCLUSION: Hemodialysis catheters placed by radiologists do not have a higher 
rate of complications or failure than catheters placed by surgeons.

